====Definition====

In Scottish, ''gowan'' is the name for the [[common daisy]] or occasionally the [[buttercup]]. It is derived from the original form ''gollan'' which is the [[marsh marigold]], the name was made famous by [[Robert Burns]] in a poem originally entitled '''"The Gowan"''' which is now known as "[[To a Mountain Daisy]]". The lakeland poet [[William Wordsworth]] also uses the word to refer to a common wayside flower indicating that the name was used in Cumbria in the 18th & 19th centuries. In Gaelic ''Gowen/Gowan'' can also mean "'''blacksmith'''"

'''Gowan''' can refer to:

* The [[Gowan Group]], a car sales company in Ireland.
* [[Lawrence Gowan]], a Canadian musician who used the stage name Gowan.
* [[Gowan River]] in [[New Zealand]]
* [[River Gowan, Cumbria]] a short tributary of the [[River Kent]] - see [[Staveley, Cumbria]]